t. Specifically, if\nfor a mixture A+B we have that ODP_B <ODP_A and \\Delta ODP = ODP_A - ODP_B,\nthen at any particular pressure where phase separation occurs, the larger the\n\\Delta ODP the lower the solubility of A in the B-rich ordered phase and the\nhigher the solubility of B in the A-rich ordered phase.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 11 Sep 2013 22:23:42 GMT"}],"update_date":"2013-09-13"}
